### -------------------------------------------------------
### System variable showcase — all 7 supported types
###
### These use the {{$name}} / {{$name args}} syntax from
### REST Client. No active environment needed; all values
### are generated at request time.
###
### Manual test:
### 1. Open this file in VS Code with curl-code active
### 2. Run each request and inspect the resolved URL,
###    headers, and body in the request viewer
### -------------------------------------------------------

### $guid — RFC 4122 v4 UUID
# Each {{$guid}} produces a unique value
GET https://httpbin.org/anything
X-Guid-1: {{$guid}}
X-Guid-2: {{$guid}}

### $timestamp — UTC Unix timestamp (seconds)
GET https://httpbin.org/anything
X-Timestamp: {{$timestamp}}

### $randomInt min max — random integer in [min, max)
GET https://httpbin.org/anything
X-Random-Small: {{$randomInt 1 10}}
X-Random-Large: {{$randomInt 1000 9999}}

### $datetime — formatted UTC datetime
GET https://httpbin.org/anything
X-Date-ISO: {{$datetime iso8601}}
X-Date-RFC: {{$datetime rfc1123}}

### $localDatetime — formatted local datetime
GET https://httpbin.org/anything
X-Local-ISO: {{$localDatetime iso8601}}
X-Local-RFC: {{$localDatetime rfc1123}}

### $processEnv — OS environment variable
# Resolves to the value of the named env var, or stays
# as {{$processEnv ...}} if the variable doesn't exist
GET https://httpbin.org/anything
X-User: {{$processEnv USER}}
X-Home: {{$processEnv HOME}}
X-Missing: {{$processEnv __THIS_SHOULD_STAY_UNRESOLVED__}}

### $dotenv — .env file variable
# Requires a .env file in the same directory as this file.
# Copy rest-client-dotenv.env to .env to test.
GET https://{{$dotenv API_HOST}}/anything
Authorization: Bearer {{$dotenv API_TOKEN}}

### All system variables in one request
POST https://httpbin.org/anything
Content-Type: application/json
X-Request-Id: {{$guid}}

{
    "id": "{{$guid}}",
    "timestamp": {{$timestamp}},
    "random": {{$randomInt 1 100}},
    "createdAt": "{{$datetime iso8601}}",
    "localTime": "{{$localDatetime rfc1123}}",
    "user": "{{$processEnv USER}}"
}

### $timestamp with offset — relative timestamps
GET https://httpbin.org/anything
X-Now: {{$timestamp}}
X-One-Hour-Ago: {{$timestamp -1 h}}
X-One-Hour-Ahead: {{$timestamp 1 h}}
X-Yesterday: {{$timestamp -1 d}}
X-Next-Week: {{$timestamp 1 w}}
X-Thirty-Min-Ago: {{$timestamp -30 m}}

### $datetime with offset — relative UTC datetimes
GET https://httpbin.org/anything
X-Now: {{$datetime iso8601}}
X-Tomorrow-ISO: {{$datetime iso8601 1 d}}
X-Yesterday-ISO: {{$datetime iso8601 -1 d}}
X-Three-Hours-Ago-RFC: {{$datetime rfc1123 -3 h}}
X-Next-Week-RFC: {{$datetime rfc1123 1 w}}

### $localDatetime with offset — relative local datetimes
GET https://httpbin.org/anything
X-Now-Local: {{$localDatetime iso8601}}
X-Tomorrow-Local: {{$localDatetime iso8601 1 d}}
X-Thirty-Min-Ago-Local: {{$localDatetime iso8601 -30 m}}
X-Next-Week-Local-RFC: {{$localDatetime rfc1123 1 w}}

### URL-encoded system variables — {{%$var}} syntax
# The {{%...}} wrapper percent-encodes the resolved value
GET https://httpbin.org/anything?user={{%$processEnv USER}}&ts={{%$timestamp}}

### Mixed: system variables + environment variables
# Requires an active curl-code environment with host and apiKey
POST {{host}}/api/data
Authorization: Bearer {{apiKey}}
Content-Type: application/json
X-Request-Id: {{$guid}}
X-Timestamp: {{$timestamp}}

{
    "id": "{{$guid}}",
    "value": {{$randomInt 1 1000}},
    "createdAt": "{{$datetime iso8601}}",
    "yesterday": "{{$datetime iso8601 -1 d}}"
}
